    "In addition, inclination of ∼ 40 deg of BLR had been favoured by these authors, in agreement with the Type 1 properties of this system, and previous constraints on the inclination derived from microlensing of the accretion disc (Poindexter and Kochanek 2010).",
    "Another system displaying salient line deformation is the large separation quad J1004+4112.",
    "The recurrent asymmetric blue-wing enhancement of C IV observed in that system has been qualitatively reproduced by Abajas et al. (2007) using a biconical geometry.",
